    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sanctae et individuae trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/7">Otto tercius</persName> servus Iesu Christi et Romanorum
                            <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus secundum voluntatem dei
                        salvatoris nostrique liberatoris. Quicquid confirmationis et proprietatis ad
                        eclesiarum dei sanctorumque suorum exaltationem prebuerimus, id nobis ad
                        aeterne beatitudinis bravium et secularis vitae profectum esse profuturum
                        verissime credimus. Igitur omnium sanctae dei aeclesiae fidelium
                        nostrorumque presentium scilicet ac futurorum agnoscat universitas, qualiter
                        nos pro dei omnipotentis amore et pro anima avie nostrae <persName
                            key="#Offersio/donatio #Queen" ref="#people/1301">Adalheidis</persName>
                        <rs key="#Queen">imperatricis</rs> augustae et ob remedium anime nostrae
                        parentumque nostrorum, rogante domno <persName key="#Abbots"><name
                                ref="Andreas">Andrea</name></persName> venerabili <rs key="#Abbots"
                            >abbate</rs>, suo <rs key="#Monasteries">coenobio</rs> ad honorem
                            <orgName
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma #Offersio/donatio #Rivers #Mountains #Villas #Curtes #Mansi #Landed_possessions #Forests #Fisheries #Saltworks #Mills #Penalty #Cereals #Wine #Oil #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Castle #Ports #Other_administrative_unit #Assembly #Angaria #Tolls #Teloneum #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Immunity #Churches #Monasteries #Abbots #Monks #Royal_slave #Royal_aldius"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3619">sancti Salvatoris</orgName> haud procul a
                        menibus <placeName key="#Palatium" ref="#places/65">Ticinensis</placeName>
                        urbis fundato per hoc nostrum imperiale preceptum, prout iuste et legaliter
                        valemus, confirmamus, quemadmodum a genitore nostro preceptali auctoritate
                        confirmata sunt, omnia que eidem venerabili loco donata collata et oblata
                        sunt, tam de <rs key="#Offersio/donatio">largifluo dono</rs> memoratae avie
                        nostrae quam etiam aliqua inscriptione cartarum aliorum hominum, cum <rs
                            key="#Castle">castellis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Villas">villis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Curtes">cortibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Churches">capellis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Churches">oratoriis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Mansi">mansis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Cereals">campis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Wine">vineis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pratis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pascuis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Mountains">montibus</rs> vallibus planiciebus <rs key="#Rivers"
                            >aquis aquarumque decursibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Fisheries">piscationibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Mills">molendinis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terris</rs> cultis et incultis <rs
                            key="#Tolls #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">ripis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Ports">portubus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Royal_slave">servis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Royal_slave">ancillis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Royal_aldius">aldionibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Royal_aldius">aldianis</rs>, verum etiam cum omnibus de quibus
                        venerabile coenobium iuste investituram habet vel habuit ex ea die qua
                        serenissima quondam avia nostr[a] <rs key="#Monks">monachos</rs> monachos
                        ibi constituit. Confirmamus quidem et firmissima traditione largimur eidem
                        monasterio sancti Salvatoris monasterium <orgName key="#Monasteries">sancti
                            Anastasii</orgName> una cum <rs key="#Curtes">curte</rs>
                        <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/139"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/342">Olonna</placeName></geogName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Montecelli</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Erbariam</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Basiliutiam</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Frisinariam</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Rivum ceruinum</placeName>, <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terram</rs>
                        de <persName key="#Landed_possessions"><name ref="Petrus Albesanus">Petro
                                Albesano</name></persName>, terram quam tenuit <persName
                            key="#Landed_possessions">
                            <name ref="Liudualdus">Liutaldus</name></persName> cum <rs key="#Mansi"
                            >manso</rs> de <placeName
                            key="#Mansi #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches">
                            <geogName key="#Mansi #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Pellentzuna</geogName></placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Tollianum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Pastorianum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Garlascum</placeName> cum <rs key="#Other_administrative_unit"
                            >districtu</rs> duum miliariorum in circuitu, <rs>viridiarium</rs> prope
                        Palatinam portam et sancti Iohannis situm cum omnibus pertinentiis suis et
                        adiacentiis tam infra civitatem Ticinensem quam extra, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Pratum regium</placeName>, insuper monasterium <orgName
                            key="#Saltworks #Oil #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1460">sanctae dei genitricis Marie</orgName> in
                        loco <placeName ref="#places/4179">Pomposa</placeName> dicto constructum et
                        omnia que in <placeName key="#Castle" ref="#places/485"><geogName
                                ref="#estates/2449">Cumaclo</geogName></placeName> eidem monasterio
                        pertinent infra <rs key="#Castle">castrum</rs> seu extra, tam in <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence 
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Reda</placeName> quam in <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence 
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/4882">Quinto</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence 
                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/3520">Corua ceruina</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence 
                                        #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/77">Uigariolo</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence 
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/4883">Zunzadega</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence 
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/4884">Ziunziano</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence 
                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/4885">Sareniano</placeName> et omnes <rs key="#Saltworks"
                            >salinas</rs>
                        <rs key="#Oil">oliveta</rs> vel omnia que ad iam dictum monasterium sanctae
                        genitricis Marie vel ad alia omnia loca que coenobio sancti salvatoris
                        domini nostri Iesu Christi pertinere videntur, tam ibi quam in caeteris
                        aliis locis nec non <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence 
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Armentaria</placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence 
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Blundi</placeName> cum pertinentiis ineffabilibus illo in proprium
                        corroboravimus. Precipientes itaque iubemus ut nullus <rs key="#Bishops"
                            >episcopus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke"> dux</rs>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">marchio</rs>
                        <rs key="#Count">comes</rs>
                        <rs key="#Viscount"> vicecomes</rs>
                        <rs key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus">castaldius</rs>
                        <rs key="#Immunity">nullaque imperii nostri magna parvaque persona de
                            [r]ebus mobilibus sive immobilibus sive de qualibet terra disvestire
                            idem monast[er]ium sine legali iudicio presumat</rs>. Sancimus insuper
                        et hac nostra imperiali [auctori]tate concedimus ut, si contigerit, quod
                        sepe accidit, quatinus abbas prenominati monasterii huius lucis habitaculum
                        deserat, liceat monachos ex sinu eiusdem eclesiae quem meliorem viderint
                        eligere in patrem, omnium episcoporum vel omnium mortalium contradictione
                        remota, nec fas sit alicui monacho ex alio monasterio ad id transitum facere
                        sine voluntate monachorum inibi deo servientium imperpetuum. Si quis autem
                        huius nostrae promulgatae auctoritatis et precepti violator extiterit sive
                        predictae eclesie sancti Salvatoris minorationem facere aut in castellis
                        villis vel aliquibus libet locis eius aribergare, <rs key="#Assembly"
                            >placitum</rs> sine eiusdem coenobii abbatis iussione ullatenus tenere
                        aut aliquam <rs key="#Angaria">angariam</rs> publicam functionem aut <rs
                            key="#Teloneum">theloneum</rs> extorquere aut tollere vel monachos de
                        aliqua re presumpserit molestare, sciat se compositurum <rs key="#Penalty"
                            >auri cocti libras mille</rs>, medietatem <rs key="#Camera_regis"
                            >camerae nostrae</rs> ac medietatem <rs
                            key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">abbati eiusdem monasterii</rs>
                        qui pro tempore fuerit, et insuper, quod ei deterius est, cum Iuda traditore
                        domini salvatoris nostri in cuius nomine iam dictum monasterium constructum
                        est, eternis deputetur incendiis. Ut autem verius credatur hoc preceptum
                        nostra auctoritate peractum, presentem paginam manu propria ut videtur infra
                        corroborantes sigillo nostro iussimus insigniri. Signum domni Ottonis (MF.)
                        caesaris invictissimi. <persName key="#Chancellor"><name ref="Eribertus"
                                >Heribertus </name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> vice <persName key="#Bishops">
                            <name ref="Petrus">Petri</name></persName> Cumani <rs key="#Bishops"
                            >episcopi</rs> recognovit. Data II. non. iul. anno dominicae
                        incarnationis M, indictione XIII, anno tercii Ottonis regnantis XVII,
                        imperantis V; actum in Papiensi <rs key="#Palatium">palacio</rs>; feliciter
                        amen. (B. D.) </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
